oai_dc:dc.dc:title: Gay Street
oai_dc:dc.dc:creator: Thompson Brothers
oai_dc:dc.dc:description: Gay Street looking south, Knoxville, TN. 3:45 p.m. May 4, 1935. Cars, buses and streetcars in the street. At left: Federal Clothing, Franklin Clothes Shop, Sherwin-Williams Paint, People's, Union Bus Terminal, Kimball's Jewelers, Fowler Brothers Furniture, Tennessee Theatre sign. At right: Hamilton Bank, Dan Cohen Shoes, Kress, Strand Theatre, Baker's Smart Shoes.
oai_dc:dc.dc:subject: Streets; Business enterprises; Automobiles; Street railroads; Traffic congestion; Buses;
